Several communities in the Western Cape have been left reeling following devastating fires which gutted their homes. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail has more details. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Families have begun the difficult process of rebuilding after three deadly blazes gutted informal settlements in Cape Town. About four people died, and thousands were displaced in the Pola Park, Masiphumele, and Du Noon fires. READ: Western Cape Fires | Hundreds of homes destroyed Most people have lost just about everything. The City of Cape Town and the Gift of the Givers have been assisting those affected by the fires. Watch the video above for more details.